05453nam a22008895i 9781501512346DE-B159720210526051534.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210526t20202020gw     fo  d z      eng d  a97815015123467 a10.1515/97815015123462doi  a(DE-B1597)537455  a(OCoLC)1158115978  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 4aP85.G735bS35 2020 7aLAN0090002bisacsh04a306.442231 aSalmon, William, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aNegative Inversion, Social Meaning, and Gricean Implicature :bA Study Across Three Texas Ethnolects /cWilliam Salmon. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter Mouton, c[2020] 4c©2020  a1 online resource (XIV, 218 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aMouton Series in Pragmatics [MSP] ;v2400tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tList of abbreviations and symbols -- tList of Tables -- tAcknowledgments -- tIntroduction -- tChapter 1 Negative inversion in Texas, in three varieties of English -- tChapter 2 Negative inversion and its contents -- tChapter 3 Negative inversion, existential sentences, and definite subjects -- tChapter 4 Negative inversion and its discontents -- tChapter 5 Negative inversion and emphatic meanings -- tChapter 6 Negative inversion is a formal idiom -- tConclusion -- tReferences -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aRelying on a wealth of new data, this book argues that long-standing puzzles of Negative Inversion (NI) syntax are not puzzles at all when viewed through the lenses of Gricean pragmatics and Labovian sociolinguistics. Focusing on sentences such as "Can't nobody lift that rock" in African American, Anglo, and Chicano Englishes in Texas, the book provides tidy solutions to problems such as: the NI’s relationship to its non-inverted counterpart, its relationship to existential “there” sentences, to modal existential sentences, to the definiteness effects surrounding its NP subject, the emphatic meaning with which it seems to be associated, and more. The book argues that such issues, which have been explored in the syntax and semantics literature since the late 1960s, are handled more fruitfully via Gricean reasoning, demographics of use, and a simple semantics. As such, the book argues that NI can be freed from the “syntactico-semantic straitjacket” into which it has often been forced. It also demonstrates ways in which pragmatic and sociolinguistic thought can be brought together to inform larger linguistic analyses.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aImplication (Logic). 0aLanguage and languagesxPhilosophy. 0aSpeech acts (Linguistics). 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aImplicature.  aNegative Inversion.  aSocial Marker.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package 2020z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2020z978311069628808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter English eBooks 2020 - UCz978311065906108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton Frontlist 2020z978311074316608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2020 Englishz978311070476108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2020z9783110704563oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97815015123600 cprintz978150151927740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150151234640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501512346423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501512346.jpg  a978-3-11-065906-1  D